Abstract = {{New statistical techniques and software have improved our ability to
   quantify fine-scale population structure. We isolated 11 microsatellite
   markers for eastern foxsnakes (Elaphe gloydi) and surveyed the
   variability of each using 115-136 individuals from one population in
   southwestern Ontario. We determined that all loci were variable and
   conformed to Hardy-Weinberg expectations and that no locus demonstrated
   linkage disequilibrium. We are using these markers to quantify the
   scale of gene flow, and to assess the effect of variable landscapes on
   connectivity and genetic diversity of three disjunct regional
   populations in the northern portion of the species' range.}},
